        "content": "**Date:** 15 May 26\n\nASK – Quality over Quantity\n\nASK expects new loan booking to grow at double digit rate this year although the company sees a slowdown in new loan booking in 2Q.\n\n1Q26 new loan booking grew 17% YoY to THB5.0b.\n\nASK is utilizing \"top-up loans\" specifically aimed at existing high-quality customers to safely boost both loan volume and yields.\n\nCash collection remains strong and see limited impact on Middle East war in Apr-May 2026.\n\nManagement guided that the problem loan from the 2022-23 have been significantly reduced via aggressive balance sheet clean-ups over recent years.\n\nThe asset quality in loan vintage of 2024-25 remain stable, thanks to its decision to pivot away from small retail borrowers and toward large corporate customers.\n\nThe CFO targets 2.0% credit cost this year and expects a credit cost to decline QoQ in the remaining quarters from 2.1% in 1Q26.\n\nCost of funds likely to gradual decline in the remaining quarters this year.\n\nOur view\n\nWe expect manageable asset quality in 2Q-3Q26. The shift in strategy toward high-quality borrowers and cleaning up older problem loans are clearly paying off through improved asset quality.\n\nWe see a low credit risk as the 2022–2023 vintage borrowers have already paid down more than 50% of their loan amounts, the remaining outstanding loans are well-covered by collateral.\n\nThis is likely result in a low Loss Given Default (LGD) and lower credit costs.\n\nDespite a minor slowdown in Q2 new loan bookings, the strategy is driving a massive earnings recovery at +45%/+22% in FY26-27E.\n\nBUY with TP THB12."
