        "label": "KKPS 13 May 26",
        "content": "**Date:** 13 May 26\n\nTHAI: 1Q26 core profit fell by 11% YoY to Bt9.0bn, beating our/consensus estimate by 5%/4%\n\n*THAI delivered a 1Q26 core profit of Bt9.0bn (-11% YoY, +32% QoQ). The result beat our/consensus estimates by 5%/4% due to higher-than-expected revenue from other business units ( ground service, catering and cargo) and slightly lower-than-expected fuel and non-fuel costs.\n\n*The company recorded tax expenses of Bt1.7bn in this quarter (vs. no tax in 1Q25). Excluding tax, EBT was Bt10.8bn, up 6% YoY and beating our estimate by 9%.\n\n*Including Bt1.0bn loss from FX loss, Bt0.6bn gain from derivatives and Bt1.4bn gain on termination of aircraft lease contracts, net profit came in at Bt10.1bn, beating our estimate by 9%\n\n*ASK declined by 2% and load factor was flat at 8% (vs 82% in 4Q24). Passenger volume declined by 3% YoY. Passenger yield was flat YoY. This leads to passenger revenue to drop by 2% YoY.\n\n*Fuel expenses decreased by 11% YoY. Meanwhile, non-fuel expenses increased by 3% YoY due to higher employee benefits (+27% YoY) and depreciation (+24% YoY). As a result, operating profit margin improve to 25.0% (vs 24.5% in 1Q25). Interest expenses decreased by 14% YoY.\n\n*1Q26 core profit accounted for 40% of our 2026E forecast of Bt22.3bn (vs 35% in 1Q25 relative to full-year 2025 profit)."
